Subject: Re: [T2] Re: Valve covers - removal and replacement

Get yourself a brake adjusting tool.  It makes dealing with the valve
cover bails much easier.  As a bonus, you can use it to adjust your
brakes!  :)

George Lyle

On Sat, 23 Mar 2002, Jason Z Upper wrote:

> Hi Folks,
>
> I agree with the "Stock is God" idea for the most part, especially when it
> comes to my engine (T4 GD 2.0 FI).  However, since I replaced my hydraulic
> lifters with solids, I've been dealing with issues of removing and replacing
> my valve covers when adjusting my valves.  The larger T4 heat exchangers and
> engine carrier make for a very tight spot, and prying the bail down and off
> with a screwdriver (a la Muir) is pretty tough.  I would think that a pair
> of bolt-on valve covers would be much easier, and the aluminum ones with
> fins would seem to improve on VW's flat-black crinkle-finish steel.
>
> Do any solid-lifter T4 owners have any tricks for getting those stubborn
> bails off and on when adjusting valves?
>
